[{"text":"### Use next/compat/router and useSearchParams for App/Pages Router compatibility

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/02-pages/04-api-reference/03-functions/use-router.mdx

This example shows how to use `useRouter` from `next/compat/router` and `useSearchParams` from `next/navigation` to create a component that functions correctly in both Next.js App and Pages directories. It includes a check for `router` being `null` and ensures router readiness before accessing search parameters, making the component adaptable during a transition to the App Router.

```jsx
import { useEffect } from 'react'
import { useRouter } from 'next/compat/router'
import { useSearchParams } from 'next/navigation'
const MyComponent = () => {
  const router = useRouter() // may be null or a NextRouter instance
  const searchParams = useSearchParams()
  useEffect(() => {
    if (router && !router.isReady) {
      return
    }
    // In `app/`, searchParams will be ready immediately with the values, in
    // `pages/` it will be available after the router is ready.
    const search = searchParams.get('search')
    // ...
  }, [router, searchParams])
  // ...
}
```

