### Access search parameters with useSearchParams in Next.js App Router

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/02-pages/04-api-reference/03-functions/use-router.mdx

This snippet illustrates a simplified component optimized for the Next.js App Router by removing any `next/compat/router` dependencies. It directly uses `useSearchParams` from `next/navigation` to retrieve URL query parameters, highlighting how to streamline code once a component is exclusively used within the App Router environment.

```jsx
import { useSearchParams } from 'next/navigation'
const MyComponent = () => {
  const searchParams = useSearchParams()
  // As this component is only used in `app/`, the compat router can be removed.
  const search = searchParams.get('search')
  // ...
}
```

