### Fetch dynamic server-side data in Next.js App Router

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/migrating/app-router-migration.mdx

This snippet shows how to fetch dynamic, non-cached data within an async React Server Component in the Next.js `app` directory, analogous to `getServerSideProps`. It defines an asynchronous function to fetch data using `fetch()` with `cache: 'no-store'` and then renders it within the component.

```tsx
// `app` directory

// This function can be named anything
async function getProjects() {
  const res = await fetch(`https://...`, { cache: 'no-store' })
  const projects = await res.json()

  return projects
}

export default async function Dashboard() {
  const projects = await getProjects()

  return (
    <ul>
      {projects.map((project) => (
        <li key={project.id}>{project.name}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  )
}
```

