### Implement Next.js Link Prefetching with Proxy in App Router

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/02-components/link.mdx

This code shows how to use the Next.js `<Link />` component in the App Router when a proxy is rewriting paths. It dynamically sets the `href` prop to the actual path (`/auth/dashboard` or `/public/dashboard`) based on authentication, while the `as` prop maintains the user-facing URL (`/dashboard`), ensuring correct prefetching.

```tsx
'use client'

import Link from 'next/link'
import useIsAuthed from './hooks/useIsAuthed' // Your auth hook

export default function Page() {
  const isAuthed = useIsAuthed()
  const path = isAuthed ? '/auth/dashboard' : '/public/dashboard'
  return (
    <Link as="/dashboard" href={path}>
      Dashboard
    </Link>
  )
}
```

