### App Router - Basic Page Structure with Layout in TypeScript

Source: https://context7.com/vercel/next.js/llms.txt

Demonstrates the fundamental App Router structure using file-system based routing where folders define routes and special files (page.tsx, layout.tsx) define UI components. The RootLayout component wraps all pages with HTML boilerplate and common layout elements. This is the foundation for building pages in Next.js 16 using the modern App Router approach.

```typescript
// app/page.tsx
export default function Page() {
  return <h1>Hello, Next.js!</h1>;
}

// app/layout.tsx
export default function RootLayout({
  children,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode;
}) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>{children}</body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

