### Disable Next.js App Router Programmatic Scroll with useRouter

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/02-components/link.mdx

When performing programmatic navigation in the Next.js App Router using `router.push()` or `router.replace()`, scrolling to the top can be disabled by passing an options object with `scroll: false`. This prevents the default scroll behavior after the navigation occurs.

